red. Please check linkage and avoid linking the same target more than once.\nW0000 00:00:1776616386.252155      55 computation_placer.cc:177] computation placer already registered. Please check linkage and avoid linking the same target more than once.\nW0000 00:00:1776616386.252158      55 computation_placer.cc:177] computation placer already registered. Please check linkage and avoid linking the same target more than once.\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"Libraries imported successfully\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":1},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 2. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)\nBefore feeding data to the Neural Network, it is crucial to understand its distribution and visualize the MRI scans. Imbalanced datasets require special strategies like undersampling or class weighting.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"data_dir = '/kaggle/input/datasets/ninadaithal/imagesoasis/Data'\n\nfilepaths = []\nlabels = []\nbinary_labels = []\n\nfor folder in os.listdir(data_dir):\n    folder_path = os.path.join(data_dir, folder)\n    if os.path.isdir(folder_path):\n        for file in os.listdir(folder_path):\n            if file.endswith('.jpg'):\n                filepaths.append(os.path.join(folder_path, file))\n                labels.append(folder)\n                binary_labels.append('Healthy' if folder == 'Non Demented' else 'Sick')\n\ndf = pd.DataFrame({'path': filepaths, 'stage': labels, 'binary': binary_labels})\n\n# VISUALIZATION 1: Data Distribution \nfig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(16, 6))\n\n# Pie Chart (Binary)\nbinary_counts = df['binary'].value_counts()\naxes[0].pie(binary_counts, labels=binary_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, colors=['#66b3ff','#ff9999'], shadow=True)\naxes[0].set_title('Binary Distribution: Healthy vs Sick', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\n\n# Bar Plot (Stages)\nstage_counts = df['stage'].value_counts().sort_values(ascending=False)\nsns.barplot(x=stage_counts.values, y=stage_counts.index, ax=axes[1], palette='magma')\naxes[1].set_title('Detailed Stage Distribution', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\naxes[1].set_xlabel('Number of MRI Scans')\naxes[1].set_ylabel('Dementia Stage')\n\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-19T16:33:38.818538Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-19T16:33:38.819062Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-19T16:33:40.735103Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-19T16:33:38.819035Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-19T16:33:40.734302Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1600x600 with 2 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":2},{"cell_type":"code","source":"#VISUALIZATION 2: Sample MRI Scans\nplt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))\nunique_stages = df['stage'].unique()\n\nfor i, stage in enumerate(unique_stages):\n    # Get one random image from each stage\n    sample_img_path = df[df['stage'] == stage]['path'].iloc[0]\n    img = cv2.imread(sample_img_path)\n    img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB) # OpenCV uses BGR, Matplotlib uses RGB\n    \n    plt.subplot(2, 2, i + 1)\n    plt.imshow(img)\n    plt.title(f'Stage: {stage}', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n    plt.axis('off')\n\nplt.suptitle('Sample MRI Scans per Category', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold', y=1.02)\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-19T16:33:40.736139Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-19T16:33:40.736468Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-19T16:33:41.440110Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-19T16:33:40.736436Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-19T16:33:41.439091Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1500x1000 with 4 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":3},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 3. Phase 1: Binary Classification (Healthy vs Sick)\n### 3.1. Data Preparation & Undersampling\nTo prevent our model from becoming biased towards the majority class (Healthy), we will perform **Undersampling**. We will randomly select a number of 'Healthy' images strictly equal to the number of 'Sick' images, creating a perfectly balanced 50/50 dataset.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"print(\"Preparation of balanced dataset for Phase 1\")\n\n\nsick_df = df[df['binary'] == 'Sick']\nhealthy_df = df[df['binary'] == 'Healthy'].sample(n=len(sick_df), random_state=42)\nbalanced_df = pd.concat([sick_df, healthy_df]).sample(frac=1, random_state=42).reset_index(drop=True)\n\n# Split into Train (80%) and Test (20%)\ntrain_df, test_df = train_test_split(balanced_df, test_size=0.2, random_state=42, stratify=balanced_df['binary'])\n\nprint(f\"Balanced Dataset ready. Total images: {len(balanced_df)}\")\nprint(f\"Training set: {len(train_df)} | Testing set: {len(test_df)}\")\n\n\ndatagen = ImageDataGenerator()\n\ntrain_generator = datagen.flow_from_dataframe(\n    dataframe=train_df, x_col='path', y_col='binary',\n    target_size=(128, 128), batch_size=32, class_mode='binary', \n    classes=['Healthy', 'Sick'], validate_filenames=False\n)\n\ntest_generator = datagen.flow_from_dataframe(\n    dataframe=test_df, x_col='path', y_col='binary',\n    target_size=(128, 128), batch_size=32, class_mode='binary', \n    classes=['Healthy', 'Sick'], shuffle=False, validate_filenames=False\n)\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-19T16:33:41.441757Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-19T16:33:41.442016Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-19T16:33:41.596131Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-19T16:33:41.441992Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-19T16:33:41.595481Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Preparation of balanced dataset for Phase 1\nBalanced Dataset ready. Total images: 38430\nTraining set: 30744 | Testing set: 7686\nFound 30744 non-validated image filenames belonging to 2 classes.\nFound 7686 non-validated image filenames belonging to 2 classes.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":4},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 3.2. Model Architecture & Training\nWe use a pre-trained **EfficientNetB0** model, unfreezing the last 20 layers for fine-tuning on our MRI scans. The output is a single neuron with a `sigmoid` activation function. We employ `EarlyStopping` and `ReduceLROnPlateau` to optimize the training process.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"print(\"Building of the Binary Classification Model\")\n\n# Load pre-trained model\nbase_model = EfficientNetB0(weights='imagenet', include_top=False, input_shape=(128, 128, 3))\nbase_model.trainable = True\nfor layer in base_model.layers[:-20]: \n    layer.trainable = False\n\n# Build architecture\nmodel_binary = Sequential([\n    base_model,\n    GlobalAveragePooling2D(),\n    BatchNormalization(),\n    Dropout(0.5),\n    Dense(1, activation='sigmoid') # 1 single output for Healthy(0) or Sick(1)\n])\n\nmodel_binary.compile(optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=1e-4), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])\n\n# Callbacks for pro-level training\nearly_stopping = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=4, restore_best_weights=True)\nreduce_lr = ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.5, patience=2, min_lr=1e-6, verbose=1)\n\nprint(\"Start of training (phase 1)\")\nhistory_binary = model_binary.fit(\n    train_generator,\n    epochs=10, \n    validation_data=test_generator,\n    callbacks=[early_stopping, reduce_lr]\n)\nprint(\"Phase 1 training complete\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-19T16:33:41.596937Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-19T16:33:41.597164Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-19T17:00:28.971967Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-19T16:33:41.597129Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-19T17:00:28.971312Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Building of the Binary Classification Model\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"I0000 00:00:1776616424.310405      55 gpu_devic