":"\nPhase 2 Classification Report:\n\n                    precision    recall  f1-score   support\n\n     Mild Dementia       0.84      0.90      0.87        97\n Moderate Dementia       0.96      1.00      0.98        98\nVery mild Dementia       0.92      0.82      0.86        98\n\n          accuracy                           0.90       293\n         macro avg       0.91      0.90      0.90       293\n      weighted avg       0.91      0.90      0.90       293\n\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":8},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 5. Model Explainability (Grad-CAM)\nIt is not enough for an AI to simply output a prediction; in a medical case, clinicians need to understand *why* that decision was made. To achieve this, implementation of **Grad-CAM** (Gradient-weighted Class Activation Mapping). \n\nThis technique generates a visual heat map over the MRI scans, highlighting the exact anatomical regions (in red and yellow) that most strongly influenced our EfficientNet model's diagnosis. This adds a crucial layer of transparency, ensuring the model relies on true biological markers (like ventricular enlargement) rather than background noise.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"\ndef make_gradcam_heatmap(img_array, model):\n    base_model = model.layers[0] # EfficientNet\n    \n    with tf.GradientTape() as tape:\n        img_tensor = tf.convert_to_tensor(img_array)\n        \n        # 1. Pass through EfficientNet and monitor the outputs\n        conv_outputs = base_model(img_tensor, training=False)\n        tape.watch(conv_outputs)\n        \n        # 2. Pass through the remaining layers (Pooling, BatchNorm, Dropout)\n        x = conv_outputs\n        for layer in model.layers[1:-1]: \n            x = layer(x, training=False)\n            \n        # 3. Apply the final layer manually\n        last_layer = model.layers[-1]\n        logits = tf.matmul(x, last_layer.kernel)\n        if last_layer.bias is not None:\n            logits += last_layer.bias\n            \n        # Target the predicted diagnosis\n        pred_index = tf.argmax(logits[0])\n        class_channel = logits[:, pred_index]\n\n    # 4. Calculate the heatmap\n    grads = tape.gradient(class_channel, conv_outputs)\n    pooled_grads = tf.reduce_mean(grads, axis=(0, 1, 2))\n    \n    conv_outputs = conv_outputs[0]\n    heatmap = conv_outputs @ pooled_grads[..., tf.newaxis]\n    heatmap = tf.squeeze(heatmap)\n    \n    # Normalize for clear visual colors\n    heatmap = tf.maximum(heatmap, 0)\n    max_heat = tf.math.reduce_max(heatmap)\n    if max_heat > 0:\n        heatmap /= max_heat \n        \n    return heatmap.numpy()\n\n# Select 3 random images from the test set\nsample_indices = random.sample(range(len(test_stage_df)), 3)\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 3, figsize=(15, 12))\n\nfor row, idx in enumerate(sample_indices):\n    img_path = test_stage_df.iloc[idx]['path']\n    true_label = test_stage_df.iloc[idx]['stage']\n    \n    # Load and format the image\n    img = tf.keras.preprocessing.image.load_img(img_path, target_size=(128, 128))\n    img_array = tf.keras.preprocessing.image.img_to_array(img)\n    img_array_batch = np.expand_dims(img_array, axis=0)\n\n    # Generate the Heatmap \n    heatmap = make_gradcam_heatmap(img_array_batch, model_stage)\n    \n    # Prediction\n    preds = model_stage.predict(img_array_batch, verbose=0)\n    pred_class_idx = np.argmax(preds[0])\n    pred_label = class_labels[pred_class_idx]\n\n    # Color superposition\n    heatmap_resized = cv2.resize(heatmap, (img_array.shape[1], img_array.shape[0]))\n    heatmap_resized = np.uint8(255 * heatmap_resized)\n    \n    \n    jet = plt.get_cmap(\"jet\")\n    \n    jet_colors = jet(np.arange(256))[:, :3]\n    jet_heatmap = jet_colors[heatmap_resized]\n    superimposed_img = jet_heatmap * 0.4 + (img_array / 255.0)\n    superimposed_img = np.clip(superimposed_img, 0, 1)\n\n    #Plotting\n    axes[row, 0].imshow(img_array / 255.0)\n    axes[row, 0].set_title(f\"Original MRI\\nTrue Stage: {true_label}\", fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n    axes[row, 0].axis('off')\n\n    axes[row, 1].imshow(heatmap_resized, cmap='jet')\n    axes[row, 1].set_title(\"AI Attention Heatmap\", fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n    axes[row, 1].axis('off')\n\n    axes[row, 2].imshow(superimposed_img)\n    axes[row, 2].set_title(f\"Superimposed MRI\\nPredicted Stage: {pred_label}\", fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n    axes[row, 2].axis('off')\n\nplt.suptitle('Grad-CAM: Visualizing the Model\\'s Diagnostic Process', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold', y=1.02)\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-19T17:34:07.810785Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-19T17:34:07.811317Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-19T17:34:11.080481Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-19T17:34:07.811287Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-19T17:34:11.079686Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1500x1200 with 9 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":13}]}